ow up, learn independence, and take on the responsibilities and disappointments of adulthood. Although the shared goals of the romantic Catholics were never realized in French politics and culture, Harrison's work offers a significant corrective to the traditional understanding of the opposition between religion and the secular republican tradition in France.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aCatholicsxHistoryx19th centuryxFrance. 0aCatholicszFrancexHistoryy19th century. 4aBiography & Autobiography. 4aEurope. 4aHistory.  achurch reform, catholic reform, modern religion, french revolution, french empire, Charles de Montalembert, Pauline Craven.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311060674440uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978080147059240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780801470592423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780801470592/original  a978-3-11-060674-4  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles